text.en_US: We call them Long Jumps here.
Perform a slash when you jump off a ledge then cancel it with a dash.
Doing so will allow you to cross distances that a normal ledge jump could not.
A single dash will sometimes not be enough.
Chain more dashes to cross even larger gaps.
You can change the direction of your jump with your dashes.
These kinds of jumps are much more tricky.
